## Practical Usage Tips
- **Parameter Adjustments**:
  | Parameter         | Default | Range | Description                              |
  |-------------------|---------|-------|------------------------------------------|
  | RSI Length        | 14      | 5-50  | Number of bars used to calculate RSI.    |
  | Oversold Level    | 30      | 20-40 | RSI level below which asset is oversold. |
  | Overbought Level  | 70      | 60-80 | RSI level above which asset is overbought.|
  | Stop Loss %       | 0.02    | 0.01-0.05 | Percentage below entry price for stop-loss.|
  | Take Profit %     | 0.04    | 0.02-0.10 | Percentage above entry price for take-profit.|

- **Risk Warnings**:
  > **Risk Warning**: Always test the strategy on historical data before live trading. Use proper position sizing to avoid significant losses.

- **Best Practices**:
  - Use this strategy on assets with **high liquidity**.
  - Combine with other indicators for confirmation.
  - Regularly monitor and adjust parameters based on market conditions.

---

## Summary
This RSI strategy is simple yet effective for identifying entry and exit points in trending markets. It includes visualizations for better understanding and risk management features to protect your capital.

